The Former Vice president Alhaji Atiku Abubakar has Charged Nigerians to put an end to the administration of the All Progressives Congress in 2023, warning that allowing APC to continue in power in the next dispensation will bring Nigeria down to its knees. Atiku stated this while addressing his party delegates in Jos on Monday at PDP Secretariat. According to him, stealing of public funds will stop if he is voted into power in 2023. -Advertisement- He said that the reckless stealing of public funds has adversely affected the economy of the nation. He said, “One of the adverse effects of unbridled corruption going on in the country has resulted in the lingering strikes in the educational system especially protracted ASUU strike resulting poor funding of education. He said, “If elected as president, I will reform the educational sector to make it in such a way it will receive adequate funding and lecturers will have no reason to go on strike. “I want to thank Plateau delegates for their unflinching support in 2019, with your support I won in 2019 but the mandate you gave was taken away. Let’s do it again in 2023” Atiku explained that “here we are again for another round of the election, it is important that PDP should get a winning candidate, I, therefore, urge delegates to make me that winning candidate at the party convention. POLL “We have been in opposition for the past eight years, can we remain in opposition again? we cannot afford to be in opposition in 2023. We must get right from the choice of candidate and return the party to governance once again. Atiku also assured Plateau delegates that he will revive the already battered economy so as to restore confidence in the private and public sectors. He also promised to stop killings and insurgency and restore security all over the country. In his remarks, the state Chairman of PDP Chris Hassan assured the aspirants that the party will not let him down at the national convention of the party.